    <so:has_sentence_context rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Sentence/3244150/864"/>
    <so:begin_index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">72</so:begin_index>
    <so:end_index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">84</so:end_index>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Sentence/3248976/835">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_schema/so_MLE#Sentence"/>
    <so:sentence_text>Only a small assemblage of charred plant remains was recovered, with just two samples that produced dense enough remains to indicate more than just background levels (yet even these yielded no more than c. 10 items per litre).</so:sentence_text>
    <so:is_part_of rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Article/3248976"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Method/Aerial_photography_3248983/32_77_95">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_schema/so_MLE#Method"/>
    <so:method_name>Aerial photography</so:method_name>
    <so:textual_span>aerial photography</so:textual_span>
    <so:has_sentence_context rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Sentence/3248983/32"/>
    <so:description>Aerial photography (or airborne imagery) is the taking of photographs from an aircraft or other airborne platforms. When taking motion pictures, it is also known as aerial videography.</so:description>
    <so:wikipedia_url>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=326279</so:wikipedia_url>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Method/Field_research_3203916/15_185_198">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_schema/so_MLE#Method"/>
    <so:method_name>Field research</so:method_name>
    <so:textual_span>field-walking</so:textual_span>
    <so:has_sentence_context rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Sentence/3203916/15"/>
    <so:description>Field research, field studies, or fieldwork is the collection of raw data outside a laboratory, library, or workplace setting. The approaches and methods used in field research vary across disciplines.</so:description>
    <so:wikipedia_url>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=5669923</so:wikipedia_url>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Sentence/3237768/440">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_schema/so_MLE#Sentence"/>
    <so:sentence_text>The probable trackway could have been sited to distinguish between two distinct areas of activity; three of the four the features with indications of ritual activity were located to the west whilst the four-posters lay further to the east.</so:sentence_text>
    <so:is_part_of rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Article/3237768"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Method/X-ray_3248978/758_84_97">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_schema/so_MLE#Method"/>
    <so:method_name>X-ray</so:method_name>
    <so:textual_span>x-radiography</so:textual_span>
    <so:has_sentence_context rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Sentence/3248978/758"/>
    <so:description>An X-ray is a form of high-energy electromagnetic radiation with a wavelength shorter than those of ultraviolet rays and longer than those of gamma rays. Roughly, X-rays have a wavelength ranging from 10 nanometers to 10 picometers, corresponding to frequencies in the range of 30 petahertz to 30 exahertz (3×1016 Hz to 3×1019 Hz) and photon energies in the range of 100 eV to 100 keV, respectively.</so:description>
    <so:wikipedia_url>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=34197</so:wikipedia_url>
  </rdf:Description>
