  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Method/Radiocarbon_dating_3248975/295_0_15">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_schema/so_MLE#Method"/>
    <so:method_name>Radiocarbon dating</so:method_name>
    <so:textual_span>Pollen analysis</so:textual_span>
    <so:has_sentence_context rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Sentence/3248975/295"/>
    <so:description>Radiocarbon dating (also referred to as carbon dating or carbon-14 dating) is a method for determining the age of an object containing organic material by using the properties of radiocarbon, a radioactive isotope of carbon. The method was developed in the late 1940s at the University of Chicago by Willard Libby.</so:description>
    <so:wikipedia_url>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=26197</so:wikipedia_url>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Goal/3203926/187_321_350">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_schema/so_MLE#Goal"/>
    <so:textual_span>seek to reveal the structures</so:textual_span>
    <so:has_sentence_context rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Sentence/3203926/187"/>
    <so:begin_index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">321</so:begin_index>
    <so:end_index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">350</so:end_index>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Sentence/3248981/1">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_schema/so_MLE#Sentence"/>
    <so:sentence_text>Joe Abrams and Drew Shotliff with contributions by Wesley Keir, John Giorgi and Alan Pipe and illustrations by Joan Lightning The excavation has confirmed the existence of the castle ditch and an attempt has been made to map its known, and putative, extent.</so:sentence_text>
    <so:is_part_of rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Article/3248981"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Method/Isotope_analysis_3238497/47_48_74">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_schema/so_MLE#Method"/>
    <so:method_name>Isotope analysis</so:method_name>
    <so:textual_span>strontium isotope analysis</so:textual_span>
    <so:has_sentence_context rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Sentence/3238497/47"/>
    <so:description>Isotope analysis is the identification of isotopic signature, abundance of certain stable isotopes of chemical elements within organic and inorganic compounds. Isotopic analysis can be used to understand the flow of energy through a food web, to reconstruct past environmental and climatic conditions, to investigate human and animal diets, for food authentification, and a variety of other physical, geological, palaeontological and chemical processes.</so:description>
    <so:wikipedia_url>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=174238</so:wikipedia_url>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Sentence/3238494/110">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_schema/so_MLE#Sentence"/>
    <so:sentence_text>It is suggested here that the quoin was deployed to demarcate the north-western corner of the nave.</so:sentence_text>
    <so:is_part_of rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Article/3238494"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Sentence/3238497/130">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_schema/so_MLE#Sentence"/>
    <so:sentence_text>However, a non-parametric Mann-Whitney test between the sexes gave a p-value of 0.6667 (W = 19), which suggests this difference is not statistically significant at a 0.05 level.</so:sentence_text>
    <so:is_part_of rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Article/3238497"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Activity/3238497/47_0_15">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_schema/so_MLE#Activity"/>
    <so:textual_span>For this study,</so:textual_span>
    <so:has_sentence_context rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Sentence/3238497/47"/>
    <so:begin_index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</so:begin_index>
    <so:end_index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">15</so:end_index>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Sentence/3248979/257">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_schema/so_MLE#Sentence"/>
    <so:sentence_text>The internal cancellous tissue is then ‘shaved’ off and also sometimes the outer surface to make the basic strip approximately 10mm wide and perhaps 100mm long, although few of this length were recovered.</so:sentence_text>
    <so:is_part_of rdf:resource="https://scholarlyontology.aueb.gr/resources/so_instances/so_MLE#Article/3248979"/>
  </rdf:Description>
